From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sophia Prototype <sophia@example.invalid>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Add SOPHIA-ROUTED-INPUT extension shell

Add a small extension shell for compositor-routed input. The initial
RouteEvent request validates the fixed wire packet and target window through
normal DIX lookup so Xnamespace resource checks still run, then returns an
explicit unsupported-event outcome until the DIX delivery entry point is wired.

This patch intentionally does not inject client events directly.
---
 Xext/meson.build                              |   1 +
 Xext/namespace/hook-ext-access.c             |   4 +
 Xext/sophia-routed-input/meson.build         |   9 +
 .../sophia-routed-input/sophia-routed-input.c | 243 ++++++++++++++++++
 meson.build                                  |   2 +
 mi/miinitext.c                               |   1 +
 miext/extinit_priv.h                         |   1 +
 7 files changed, 261 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 Xext/sophia-routed-input/meson.build
 create mode 100644 Xext/sophia-routed-input/sophia-routed-input.c

diff --git a/Xext/meson.build b/Xext/meson.build
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/Xext/meson.build
+++ b/Xext/meson.build
@@ -41,3 +41,4 @@ subdir('shm')
 subdir('xv')
 subdir('xres')
 subdir('xtest')
+subdir('sophia-routed-input')
diff --git a/Xext/namespace/hook-ext-access.c b/Xext/namespace/hook-ext-access.c
index 0000000000..0000000000 100644
--- a/Xext/namespace/hook-ext-access.c
+++ b/Xext/namespace/hook-ext-access.c
@@ -24,6 +24,10 @@ void hookExtAccess(CallbackListPtr *pcbl, void *unused, void *calldata)
     if (streq(param->ext->name, XNS_EXTENSION_NAME))
         goto reject;
 
+    /* compositor-only extension: hidden outside the privileged root namespace */
+    if (streq(param->ext->name, "SOPHIA-ROUTED-INPUT"))
+        goto reject;
+
     switch (param->ext->index + EXTENSION_BASE) {
         /* unrestricted access */
         case EXTENSION_MAJOR_BIG_REQUESTS:
